						               													<description>A word game for everyone!&amp;#10;Move on the board by jumping from one tile to another, choose the right letters and write the longest word!   A game of language skill and strategy to train the minds of young and old.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Mix the letter tiles and arrange them in the center of the table forming a 5x5 square.  Each player takes a marker, a word-form board and a joker triangle.  Procedure The youngest player places the black placeholder on a letter-card of his choice.  Each player then chooses a letter (present in the selected tile) and writes it on their word-form board (in one of the circles).  Then the next player moves the placeholder onto another letter-card adjacent to the previous one (the movement can take place by one step).  The process is repeated up to that the players have not completed the six letters on their wordform board.  At this point the players, within 30 seconds, must write a meaningful word using their transcribed letters.  Each player will earn as many points as there are letters in the written word.  The score achieved by each player must be written in the corresponding space on the scorecard.  Jolly Triangle During a round, players can play the joker by placing the triangle of their color on the active letter-tile: in the word formation phase, they will be able to use a letter present in that tile an infinite number of times.  New round The trailing player takes the placeholder and starts a new round in the same way as the previous one.  The game continues and ends when a player reaches 20 points (or more or less at the players' choice).  He will be the winner!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
